orter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur/Porter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur") (media:description nil "19 of those killed were aged under five ... Oklahoma City bombing, 1995. Photograph: Porter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2011/3/3/1299157087173/Oklahoma-City-bombings-19-007.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Porter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur/Porter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur") (media:description nil "Victims of US terror attacks. 19 of those killed in Oklahoma in 1995 were aged under five. Photograph: Porter/Keystone USA / Rex Featur")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366204408732/US-terror-attacks-interac-010.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "CartoDB/Guardian") (media:description nil "US terror attacks interactive map. Click image to explore it"))) (item nil (title nil "Margaret Thatcher's funeral: 23 things you could pay for with £10m") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2013/apr/16/margaret-thatcher-funeral-10-million") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/83832?ns=guardian&pageName=Graphic%3Amargaret-thatcher-funeral-10-million%3A1894330&ch=News&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Margaret+Thatcher%2CPublic+sector+cuts+%28Society%29%2CLibraries%2CUnemployment+%28Society%29%2CUK+news%2CNHS+%28Society%29%2CMilitary+UK&c5=Unclassified%2CSkills+Education%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CHealth+Society&c6=Simon+Rogers%2CMona+Chalabi%2CAmi+Sedghi&c7=2013%2F04%2F16+02%3A46&c8=1894330&c9=Blog&c10=Blogpost&c13=&c19=GUK&c25=Datablog&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Margaret+Thatcher%27s+funeral%3A+23+things+you+could+pay+for+with+%C2%A310m&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FNews%2Fblog%2FDatablog\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Margaret Thatcher's funeral will cost around £10m, although we won't know the exact figure - and how much of it is being spent by the state - until afterwards. What else can £10m pay for? Here are some ideas …</p><h2>322 nurses for a year</h2><p><em>Based on a median annual salary of £31,095</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>272 secondary school teachers for a year</h2><p><em>Based on a median annual salary of £36,789</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>320 fire officers for a year</h2><p><em>Based on a median annual salary of £31,258</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>269 paramedics for a year</h2><p><em>Based on a median annual salary of £37,164</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Four months' worth of the state's contribution to the Monarchy</h2><p><em>Per year it costs the UK £32m</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>7,042 households' electricity and gas bills</h2><p><em>Based on a typical annual dual fuel bill of £1,420 each</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>25,773 households' annual water bills</h2><p><em>£388 per household average</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>44 libraries</h2><p><em>£963,284,000 spent on libraries in 2011-12 - for 4,265 'service points'</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>177,777 jobseekers' allowance claimants</h2><p><em>On £56.25 a week each</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>1,199 students' annual tuition fees</h2><p><em>Average tuition fees are £8,338</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>10 days of arts spending</h2><p><em>Annual spending on the arts for a year: £398m</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Two years of UK foreign aid to Iraq</h2><p><em>It costs the UK £5m a year</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Two and a half Leveson Inquiries</h2><p><em>The cost of the Inquiry was £3.9m</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Two weeks of the BBC World Service</h2><p><em>The annual FCO spending on the World Service is £255m</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Two years of the Wales Office</h2><p><em>It costs the UK £5m a year</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>152 MPs' basic salaries</h2><p><em>Before allowances, this is £65,738 each</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>16,949,152 pints of milk - enough to give everyone in London two pints each</h2><p><em>Based on a price of 59p each</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>60% of a Trident missile</h2><p><em>Cost: £16.8m each</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>49 days of British forces in the Falklands</h2><p><em>Based on annual spending of £75m</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>Flights for everyone in the Falklands to the UK and back and a trip up the Shard each. Three times over</h2><p><em>Return flight (plus tax): £1,208, Shard: £24.95</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>400 black Asprey 'Margaret Thatcher' handbags</h2><p><em>Her handbag shown above sold for £25,000 at auction</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>6,079 duck houses for MPs claiming on expenses</h2><p><em>The amount that former Conservative MP Peter Viggers claimed for a floating duck house was £1,645</em><br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p><h2>11,111 public health funerals</h2><p><em>These are free funerals for poor people or those without any relatives or money, each costs the state £900</em></p><p><a name=\"data\"></p><h2>Download the data</h2><p></a></p><p>• <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AonYZs4MzlZbdEp0NUhjMnZ1UEVXWlFqeFgtUWc3cWc&usp=sharing\">DATA: download the full spreadsheet</a></p><h2>More data</h2><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data\">M