 "guardian.co.uk") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Boston") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Boston Marathon explosions") (pubDate nil "Tue, 16 Apr 2013 13:12:00 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/datablog/2013/apr/16/boston-marathon-explosions-competitors-country") (dc:creator nil "Simon Rogers") (dc:subject nil "World news") (dc:date nil "2013-04-16T13:27:59Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407282481") (media:keywords nil "Boston Marathon explosions, United States, Boston, Massachusetts") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2013/4/15/1366058460971/Boston-marathon-005.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Boston Globe/Getty Images") (media:description nil "Boston marathon. Photograph: Boston Globe/Getty Images")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/audio/video/2013/4/15/1366054419770/Boston-marathon-runners-010.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Dominick Reuter/Reuters") (media:description nil "Boston marathon runners. Where were they from and who were they? Photograph: Dominick Reuter/Reuters"))) (item nil (title nil "Boston explosions: information and misinformation") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2013/apr/16/data-store-boston-marathon-explosions") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/58830?ns=guardian&pageName=Graphic%3Adata-store-boston-marathon-explosions%3A1894549&ch=News&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Boston+Marathon+explosions+%28News%29%2CWorld+news&c5=Unclassified%2CNot+commercially+useful&c6=Mona+Chalabi%2CJohn+Burn-Murdoch&c7=2013%2F04%2F16+01%3A25&c8=1894549&c9=Blog&c10=Blogpost&c13=Show+and+Tell+%28dataviz+series%29&c19=GUK&c25=Datablog&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FNews%2Fblog%2FDatablog\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">No arrests have yet been made and no groups have claimed responsibility for the explosions at the Boston marathon. Social media, both good and bad, has filled the information space <br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/us-news-blog/2013/apr/16/boston-marathon-explosions-hunt-begins-for-perperators-live-updates\">Live updates on Boston marathon explosions from Paul Owen</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/interactive/2013/apr/16/boston-marathon-explosion-map-interactive\">Guardian interactive tool on the blasts</a></p><p>At around 2.50pm ET (7.50pm GMT) two explosions were detonated near the finish line of the <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston\">Boston Marathon</a>. Since then, there has been a frantic attempt to collect and visualise information about events and the number of victims. Here, look at some of the tools used to gain clarity about what happened, assist those seeking help and those providing it.</p><h2>Information</h2><p><a href=\"http://live.boston.com/Event/Live_blog_Explosion_in_Copley_Square/72936164\">Boston.com</a> quickly set up two Google forms in response to the explosion: one '<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/a/guardian.co.uk/forms/d/1r2dbf7q2sIiiQWynPNgH74qNeheNycTyk7hXue9AJhs/viewform\">need a place to stay</a>' and one '<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/a/guardian.co.uk/forms/d/1dqIKVq6IqX4BVXqOW_a9-qmXt1KJ_4Nu3NPNnC1g1mw/viewform\">I have a place to offer</a>'. Users were also able to see the information already submitted by others, including phone numbers and e-mail addresses so that they could contact others directly.</p><p>Using <a href=\"http://www.tableausoftware.com/\">Tableau</a>, we've shown how the number of offers of accommodation has changed over time as the link to the spreadsheet was shared on social media, news and official websites. The graph shows how in the space of two minutes, the number of offers increased from 3 to 85 and stayed high over the next ten minutes. This peaked again around an hour later, when 33 offers to help those needing shelter were received via Google. </p><p>As has been the case in the aftermath of other crises (such as the Mumbai attacks in 2011), social media has played a central role. Boston's mayor's office quickly tweeted information about which areas to avoid and Boston's police department used its twitter account to request information from members of the public, announce street closures and press conferences.</p><p>In fact, not tweeting was a decision which had to be <a href=\"https://twitter.com/BostonFire\">publicly justified</a> by Boston's fire department.</p><p><a href=\"http://trendsmap.com/\">Trendsmap</a> tracks twitter trends in real time and maps them using the location in users' twitter profiles. As it's so soon after the event, several of these visualisations are still being developed, however as this <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BlL-foAGizk&feature=player_embeddedhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BlL-foAGizk&feature=player_embedded\">video after the Samoa earthquake demonstrates</a>, Trendsmap is also able to show how twitter trends evolve over time.</p><p>Because it can process tweets in all languages, Trendsmap can also show global twitter trends. These screengrabs (taken at 11am GMT) show that the Boston marathon explosion was not just the main topic of American twitter users, but also those in Western Europe, South Africa, Australia, East Asia and the Middle East.</p><p>Maps have also been important in order to understand the impact of the explosion at the micro-level. This interactive map developed by The Guardian shows where the devices were detonated and includes verified pictures taken after the blasts. </p><p><strong></strong></p><h2>Misinformation</h2><p>Inevitably, a small number of opportunists have sought to use the explosions to further their own agendas. A twitter account promising a $1 donation to victims for every retweet received more than 50,000 retweets and 800 favourites before being <a href=\"http://sacramento.cbslocal.com/2013/04/15/fake-boston-marathon-twitter-account-appears-after-explosions-quickly-suspended/\">suspended</a> by Twitter. Another account, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HopeForBoston?tw_i=323948385952473088&tw_p=tweetembed\">@HopeforBoston</a>, claims to have images of children killed in Boston's explosions who were running for victims of last year's <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/newtown-shooting\">Newtown shooting</a>. Despite receiving more than 100,000 retweets, the images are fake and were taken from a <a href=\"http://www.saxonscope.com/top-stories/2012/05/20/hundreds-turn-out-for-3rd-annual-joe-cassella-5k/\">school run</a> in May last year.</p><h2>More open data</h2><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data\">Data journalism and data visualisations from the Guardian</a></p><h2>World government data</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world-government-data\">Search the world's government data with our gateway</a></p><h2>Development and aid data</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data-store/global-development-data/search?q=\">Search the world's global development data with our gateway</a></p><h2>Can you do something with this data?</h2><p>• <strong>Flickr</strong> Please post your visualisations and mash-ups on our <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/groups/1115946@N24/\">Flickr group</a><br />• Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:data@guardian.co.uk\">data@guardian.co.uk</a></p><p><strong>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/page/2009/jun/17/1\">Get the A-Z of data</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data-store\">More at the Datastore directory</a></strong><br /><strong>• <a href=\"http://twitter.com/GuardianData\">Follow us on Twitter</a></strong><br /><strong>• <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/Guardian-data/155291341187950\">Like us on Facebook</a></strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/boston-marathon-explosions\">Boston Marathon explosions</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/mona-chalabi\">Mona Chalabi</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/john-burn-murdoch\">John Burn-Murdoch</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/643782/s/2ac774b9/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fdatablog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F16%2Fdata-store-boston-marathon-explosions&t=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fdatablog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F16%2Fdata-store-boston-marathon-explosions&t=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fdatablog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F16%2Fdata-store-boston-marathon-explosions&t=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fdatablog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F16%2Fdata-store-boston-marathon-explosions&t=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fdatablog%2F2013%2Fapr%2F16%2Fdata-store-boston-marathon-explosions&t=Boston+explosions%3A+information+and+misinformation\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644559736/u/49/f/643782/c/34708/s/2ac774b9/kg/342/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644559736/u/49/f/643782/c/34708/s/2ac774b9/kg/342/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644559736/u/49/f/643782/c/34708/s/2ac774b9/kg/342/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "Blogposts") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "World news") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "guardian.co.uk") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/world")) "Boston Marathon explosions") (pubDate nil "Tue, 16 Apr 2013 12:25:00 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2013/apr/16/data-store-boston-marathon-explosions") (dc:creator nil "Mona Chalabi, John Burn-Murdoch") (dc:subject nil "News") (dc:date nil "2013-04-16T13:25:47Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407274891") (media:keywords nil "Boston Marathon explosions, World news") (media:content ((height . "82") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366110607128/snmall2.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "guardian.co.uk")) (media:content ((height . "268") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366110627793/snmall.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "guardian.co.uk")) (media:content ((height . "161") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366111049978/New_police.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Twitter")) (media:content ((height . "162") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366111135093/fire.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Twitter")) (media:content ((height . "256") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366111333325/America_focus.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Trendsmap")) (media:content ((height . "199") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366111461443/world.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Trendsmap")) (media:content ((height . "278") (lang . " ") (type . "image/png") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/16/1366112374829/guarinteractive.png")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Guardian") (media:description nil "Graphics by Paddy Allen and Ranjit Dhaliwal. Click to go to interactive page."))) (item nil (title nil "UK inflation since 1948") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2009/mar/09/inflation-economics") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/2966?ns=guardian&pageName=Graphic%3Ainflation-economics%3A1176852&ch=News&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Inflation+%28Business%29%2CEconomics+%28Business%29%2CQuantitative+easing+%28Business%29%2CFinancial+crisis+%28Business%29%2CDeflation%2CUK+news%2CEconomic+policy%2CBusiness%2CBank+of+England+%28Business%29%2CGovernment+data+%28Politics%29%2COffice+for+National+Statistics+ONS%2CGeorge+Osborne%2CMervyn+King&c5=Credit+Crunch%2CBusiness+Markets%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CBudget&c6=Ami+Sedghi%2CSimon+Rogers&c7=2009%2F03%2F09+05%3A05&c8=1176852&c9=Blog&c10=Blogpost&c13=&c19=GUK&c25=Datablog&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=UK+inflation+since+1948&c66=News&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FNews%2FNews%2Fblog%2FDatablog\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Inflation in the UK has remained unchanged from February. Get the full data over time, see how it compares with pay - and understand the new measures<br />• <a href=\"http://www.guprod.gnl/news/datablog/interactive/2012/may/22/inflation-cpi-rpi-interactive\">Interactive inflation data explorer from Timetric<br /></a>• <a href=\"#data\">Get the data</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data\">More data journalism and data visualisations from the Guardian</a></p><h2>How pay has fallen behind inflation</h2><p><strong></strong></p><p>UK inflation <a href=\"http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/cpi/consumer-price-indices/march-2013/stb---consumer-price-indices---march-2013.html#tab-Key-points\">has remained unchanged at 2.8% for March 2013</a>, the Office for National Statistics (ONS) revealed today. The ONS state that \"over the last six months, the CPI 12-month rate has been particularly stable, standing at 2.7% for four months followed by 2.8% for February and March 2013\". <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/katieallen\">Katie Allen</a> <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2013/apr/16/inflation-newspapers-books\">writes today</a>: </p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p>The rate of inflation stayed at its highest level for almost a year in March, keeping up the squeeze on consumers.</p><p>The annual rate of consumer price inflation held at 2.8%, according to official data. That is the highest since last May and in line with economists' forecasts.</p></blockquote><p>There is more than one method of measuring inflation. Up until today, we were mostly concerned with the consumer price index (CPI) measure - which is the government's favoured one. In September 2011, when the CPI stood at 5.2%, it had never been higher in recorded history. The CPI is important because it is used for uprating pensions, wages and benefits.</p><p>The second measure is the retail price index (RPI) which has now been dumped as a national statistic (although the ONS will keep publishing it for a while).</p><p>Instead we now have CPIH, which includes owner occupiers' housing costs and RPIJ - the new version of the Retail Prices Index (RPI). If you're interested, the old RPI measure stands at 3.3% this month, up from 3.2% last month.</p><p>This is how the indexes compare:</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>We have also added in pay data - and you can see how inflation has been racing ahead of average earnings. Even with the falls in previous months, people's wages are not increasing as fast as the cost of living.</p><p>There are some important differences between the two ways the ONS measures inflation. The government prefers the <strong>consumer price index</strong>, which also includes services, housing, electricity, food, and transportation, but the <strong>retail price index</strong> covers more items. The RPI includes housing costs and is used for many pay negotiations and used to be used for pension payments. We've included both here - just click on the links on the spreadsheet. <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2012/mar/13/inflation-basket-goods-2012-full-list\">You can get the full list of items in the inflation basket here</a>.</p><p>If you want to see how different elements of inflation have changed, check out this <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/interactive/2012/may/22/inflation-cpi-rpi-interactive\">interactive data explorer from Timetric</a>.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>We have gathered all the data for inflation since June 1948. Let us know what you can do with this data.</p><p>To find out more about how RPI and CPI differ, explore <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/interactive/2012/may/22/inflation-cpi-rpi-interactive\">this set of interactive charts</a>. The graphics show a breakdown of the different measures and components of inflation, and you can compare rates between countries.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><a name=\"data\"></p><h2><br />Download the data</h2><p></a></p><p><a href=\"http://spreadsheets.google.com/ccc?key=pXMFQ3e4aFY11oQkT_7FhZg\">DATA: UK inflation since the 1940s - CPI and RPI</a><br /><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/interactive/2009/mar/24/rpi-inflation\">INTERACTIVE: how we visualised the data</a></p><h2>More data</h2><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data\">More data journalism and data visualisations from the Guardian</a></p><h2>World government data</h2><p><strong></strong></p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world-government-data\">Search the world's government data with our gateway</a></p><h2>Development and aid data</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data-store/global-development-data/search?q=\">Search the world's global development data with our gateway</a></p><h2>Can you do something with this data?</h2><p>• <strong>Flickr</strong> Please post your visualisations and mash-ups on our <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/groups/1115946@N24/\">Flickr group</a><br />• Contact us at <a href=\"mailto:data@guardian.co.uk\">data@guardian.co.uk</a></p><p><strong>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/technology/page/2009/jun/17/1\">Get the A-Z of data</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data-store\">More at the Datastore directory</a></strong><br /><strong>• <a href=\"http://twitter.com/guardiandata\">Follow us on Twitter</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/Guardian-data/155291341187950\">Like us on Facebook</a></strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/inflation\">Inflation</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/economics\">Economics</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/quantitative-easing\">Quantitative easing</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/financial-crisis\">Financial crisis</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/deflation\">Deflation</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/politics/economy\">Economic policy</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/bankofenglandgovernor\">Bank of England</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/politics/government-data\">Government data</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk/office-for-national-statistics\">Office for National Statistics</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/politics/georgeosborne\">George Osborne</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/mervyn-king\">Mervyn King</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/ami-sedghi\">Ami Sedghi</a></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/simonrogers\">Simon Rogers</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/643782/s/29c1c571/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/viral/sendEmail.cfm?lang=en