 list.</p><p><a href=\"http://manyeyes.alphaworks.ibm.com/manyeyes/visualizations/doctor-who-villains\">inspired by the work of xxnapoleonsolo on Many Eyes</a>, we tried to put together the definitive list of every Doctor Who villain and monster - ever. <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2010/jul/20/doctor-whos-enemies\">We had no idea there were so many</a>. Here's our Tableau visualisation of them so far.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>We've been adding loads of new creatures and people - thanks to your suggestions - and we probably still have some more to go. </p><p>So, here's a list of all the Doctor Who villains since the very first episode in 1963. Whether it's to help you put your bet on what will make a reappearance next series or just to satisfy hard-core Whovians, hopefully this will help out.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>The chart however doesn't include villains exclusively in Doctor Who books, audio books and spin-off shows - only the televised serials and only enemies, as opposed to protagonists. See the comments below for more details.</p><p>We're bound to have missed someone - or even got some details wrong. So let us know in the comments field below - and tell us if you do anything with the <a href=\"#data\">data</a>. We've extended the comments date so we can keep going with the new series.</p><p>Which was your favourite? Download the data and let us know what you can do with it.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><a name=\"data\"></p><h2>Download the data</h2><p></a><br />• <a href=\"http://spreadsheets.google.com/ccc?key=0AonYZs4MzlZbdHJNSVh6clE4MVR4OHhqZWs4WGpSZlE&hl=en\">DATA: download the full datasheet</a></p><h2>More data</h2><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/data\">More data journalism and data visualisations from the Guardian</a></p><h2>World government data</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world-government-data\">Search the world's government data with our gateway</a></p><h2>Development and aid data</h2><p>• <a h