009/nov/25/gdp-uk-1948-growth-economy") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/35473?ns=guardian&pageName=Graphic%3Agdp-uk-1948-growth-economy%3A1176842&ch=Business&c3=GU.co.uk&c4=Economic+growth+%28GDP%29+UK%2CEconomic+policy%2CEconomics+%28Business%29%2CQuantitative+easing+%28Business%29%2CFinancial+crisis+%28Business%29%2CBusiness%2CUK+news%2CGovernment+data+%28Politics%29%2COffice+for+National+Statistics+ONS%2CGeneral+election+2010&c5=Credit+Crunch%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CBusiness+Markets&c6=Simon+Rogers&c7=2009%2F03%2F09+05%3A00&c8=1176842&c9=Blog&c10=Blogpost&c13=&c19=GUK&c25=Datablog&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=UK+GDP+since+1955&c66=Business&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FBusiness%2FBusiness%2FEconomic+growth+%28GDP%29\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Gross domestic product is the economic output of Britain. See how it has changed over time<br />• <a href=\"#data\">Get the data</a><br />• <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/interactive/2012/sep/27/recessions-compared-1930-2008\">Interactive chart: How does this recession compare?</a><br />• <a href=\"#chart\">Chart: GDP change since 2008</a></p><p><strong></strong></p><p>The possibility of a triple-dip recession seems to have inched closer as GDP for the last three months of 2012 was confirmed to have dropped by 0.3%. If the economy shrinks again in the first quarter of this year, that will plunge the UK into its third recession in the past five years, an unprecedented triple-dip.</p><p>You can find out who gets <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/news/datablog/2012/oct/25/pre-release-access-good-news-david-cameron\">access to this data early too by clicking here.</a></p><p>The ONS explains the data as follows:</p><blockquote class=\"quoted\"><p><br />• Household final consumption expenditure increased by 0.4% in volume terms in the latest quarter revised up from the 0.2% increase previously estimated<